Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.22,0:00:05.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.45,0:00:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out of the money again?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.98,0:00:08.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I must be unlucky today...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.63,0:00:11.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.51,0:00:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got this fruit parfait in order to enjoy an authentic tropical mood!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.32,0:00:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why won't you read your horse racing\Npaper at the detective agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.78,0:00:21.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that strawberry look delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.16,0:00:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're not eating it, I'll take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.49,0:00:26.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.58,0:00:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was saving that for last, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.00,0:00:30.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lemme have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.71,0:00:32.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.59,0:00:37.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.55,0:00:38.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This strawberry was the spark.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.92,0:00:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't have a single clue at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.97,0:00:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think this was the start of a sweet and sour major case...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.31,0:00:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the deciding moment that determines your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.11,0:00:53.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cannot lie to yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.41,0:00:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're finally out of Japan...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.20,0:00:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in deep-yearning London for a grand case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.36,0:00:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.98,0:01:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.03,0:01:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,250)}His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.64,0:02:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.64,0:02:54.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was looking forward to eating it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:02:59.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with this cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.90,0:03:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do cats eat strawberries?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.15,0:03:04.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just rolling it around and playing with it, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.90,0:03:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, where'd this cat come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.83,0:03:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,YOU LITTLE—!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.20,0:03:17.70,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Oh, Venus!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.29,0:03:19.71,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Venus!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.13,0:03:23.38,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Oh, I'm so glad you're unhurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.21,0:03:26.38,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Thank you so much for finding her!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.84,0:03:28.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think she's thanking us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.93,0:03:31.09,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}My father is a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.22,0:03:32.18,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.18,0:03:33.55,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}How admirable!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.60,0:03:36.89,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}I'm fond of crime novels myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.89,0:03:39.31,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}And I love to hear stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.64,0:03:43.11,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}But I have a flight to catch—such a shame...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.27,0:03:44.77,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.77,0:03:46.86,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}May I invite you to my home?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.86,0:03:48.28,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}In London.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.28,0:03:51.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's she saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.57,0:03:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.91,0:03:55.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She spoke so quickly that I didn't get most of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:03:56.87,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Wow, that's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.45,0:04:00.08,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Oh, you accept?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.08,0:04:02.12,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Then, when can you visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.29,0:04:05.42,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}We don't have school next weekend!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.46,0:04:06.84,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Oh, good!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.59,0:04:10.80,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Then, I will arrange your trip as soon as I return home!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.51,0:04:13.89,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}That brat can speak English?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.89,0:04:14.89,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Looks that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.10,0:04:16.47,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.60,0:04:17.81,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Sure! All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.97,0:04:19.56,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Thank you, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.73,0:04:24.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're going to the UK next weekend?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.44,0:04:27.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, what about school and everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.29,0:04:29.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.40,0:04:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both Teitan Elementary and Teitan High will be on a four-day\Nbreak because the weekend overlaps with the holidays.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.62,0:04:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran and Uncle are excited about it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.39,0:04:41.90,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What's more, it seems Diana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the owner of the cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.92,0:04:44.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Happens to be really wealthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.42,0:04:44.01,Signs,,0,0,0,,Diana Kingstone (58)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.92,0:04:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she's paying for our travel expenses and our hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.42,0:04:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't that something!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.67,0:04:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be able to visit London, your heart's desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.09,0:04:53.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.97,0:04:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad's taken me to a lot of places overseas, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.64,0:04:58.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've never been to London!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.68,0:05:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, I'll have to go to Baker Street...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.44,0:05:05.90,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hyde Park
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.56,0:05:05.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the place where Holmes and Watson strolled — Hyde Park...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.59,0:05:10.91,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And then the British Museum where Holmes\Nwould go to investigate things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:10.58,Signs,,0,0,0,,The British Museum
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.44,0:05:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if we have time, maybe even the stage for\NThe Hound of the Baskervilles—Dartmoor...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.32,0:05:20.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then where Holmes and his nemesis\NProfessor Moriarty fell—Reichenbach Falls!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.50,0:05:25.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are so many places I want to go, I almost can't decide!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.25,0:05:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.59,0:05:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.80,0:05:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your passport.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.88,0:05:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I completely forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.93,0:05:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now look here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.55,0:05:41.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Edogawa Conan is Kudou Shinichi's\Nshrunken form thanks to that poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.52,0:05:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really shouldn't exist, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.06,0:05:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way someone like that could\Nfly overseas without a care in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.15,0:05:50.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess you're right, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.82,0:05:53.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.65,0:05:55.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you do something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.78,0:05:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Make me a fake passport or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.20,0:05:59.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.41,0:06:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.83,0:06:02.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.33,0:06:06.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finally get the{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce to pilgrimage to the\NHolmes mecca and I have to stay home!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.67,0:06:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that even fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.25,0:06:09.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.67,0:06:12.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as going, there is but one way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.55,0:06:14.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.55,0:06:17.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have to promise to follow my instructions down to the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.55,0:06:19.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.94,0:06:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.86,0:06:32.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First class is so spacious!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.36,0:06:35.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just how ridiculously rich is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.82,0:06:37.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That old lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:39.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's too bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.58,0:06:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} couldn't come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.79,0:06:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.87,0:06:46.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said something suddenly came up that he had to do, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.53,0:06:47.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.65,0:06:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's coming on the next flight with Professor Agasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.16,0:06:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to think she'd pay for the professor's travel as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.49,0:06:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Diana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really is a wonderful person!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.76,0:06:59.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she's not paying for souvenirs, so\Ndon't spend your money mindlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.01,0:07:03.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet you're going to buy a mountain of stuff, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.31,0:07:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For that Holmes geek detective brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.73,0:07:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't planning to buy a mountain load!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.69,0:07:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I bet he'd rather be there himself than get souvenirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.91,0:07:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would've been great if Shinichi could've come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.33,0:07:28.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't the air conditioning on this plane a bit too strong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.62,0:07:31.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't act too conspicuous!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.46,0:07:35.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and them find out we're on the same flight they are...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.21,0:07:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.80,0:07:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're in first class.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.93,0:07:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They won't come back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.51,0:07:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was thanks to Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s brilliant suggestion...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.72,0:07:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To use the drug to only temporarily return you to Kudou\NShinichi in order to pass the departure inspection!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.19,0:07:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm thankful...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.71,0:07:56.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.07,0:07:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm giving you two pills—one for going and one for coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.45,0:08:03.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The approximate duration of the drug's effect is 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.16,0:08:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need to calculate the correct time to take the drug...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:09.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that you can return to your present form\Nright after getting through the UK customs!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.58,0:08:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is it all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.08,0:08:13.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I'm taking the professor with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.09,0:08:14.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.38,0:08:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be staying at Yoshida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s place in the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.72,0:08:20.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.51,0:08:23.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you know this already, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.51,0:08:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you were to take it again before the time is\Nup, the effective window would be halved.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.10,0:08:30.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And don't forget that you would never be able to return home!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.39,0:08:32.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.49,0:08:36.74,Signs,,0,0,0,,Heathrow Airport (UK)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.03,0:08:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.07,0:08:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They still haven't come out yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.91,0:08:48.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their plane should've landed a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.87,0:08:49.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.87,0:08:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.46,0:08:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When did you get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.25,0:08:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.46,0:08:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.38,0:09:00.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The effect of the drug took longer to wear off than anticipated...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.97,0:09:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forcing me to wait it out in the restroom for thirty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.44,0:09:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.85,0:09:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We still have some time before we meet\Nwith that rich lady at the hotel tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.48,0:09:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about we do some sightseeing around London!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.44,0:09:16.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where do you want to go, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.86,0:09:18.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, that'd be...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.66,0:09:21.36,Signs,,0,0,0,,Sherlock Holmes Museum
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.95,0:09:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected of the Sherlock Holmes Museum!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.07,0:09:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Awwwwsome!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.87,0:09:32.54,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Can I take this seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.66,0:09:34.04,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.67,0:09:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excellent!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.01,0:09:44.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet Shinichi would be just as cheerful if he were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.39,0:09:48.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.35,0:09:50.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have said in his e-mail he didn't want any souvenirs, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.06,0:09:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have a list of things to buy for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.64,0:09:55.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.73,0:09:57.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't I give him a surprise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.69,0:10:05.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's from Shinichi's phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.53,0:10:06.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.74,0:10:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Ran!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.08,0:10:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.67,0:10:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.46,0:10:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess where I am right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.92,0:10:24.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm at 221B Baker Street!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.80,0:10:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.01,0:10:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did e-mail me saying you were going to London, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.97,0:10:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with that half-hearted reaction?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.35,0:10:35.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try and be a little jealous!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.19,0:10:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.94,0:10:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just so busy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.85,0:10:40.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.02,0:10:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there anywhere that you'd like me to take a photo of for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.32,0:10:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure which places you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.28,0:10:48.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I already said I didn't need anything like that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.37,0:10:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.37,0:10:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, I'm hanging up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.46,0:10:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.16,0:10:58.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stupid Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.46,0:11:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stupid, stupid, STUPID!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.38,0:11:05.92,default01,,0,0,0,,{\b2}I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.01,0:11:08.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.13,0:11:11.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.51,0:11:13.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man, did I just make her mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.06,0:11:23.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're leaving already?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.75,0:11:24.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.98,0:11:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've enjoyed everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.07,0:11:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the souvenir shop is next door too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.70,0:11:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if Holmes were really here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.95,0:11:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd stay for days and weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.83,0:11:36.62,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}You're lying to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.62,0:11:38.58,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}I know Holmes is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.46,0:11:41.04,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Let me see him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.29,0:11:44.75,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}I'm sorry, but Mr. Holmes is out on an investigation...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.75,0:11:46.76,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}What kind of investigation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.88,0:11:48.51,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Well, he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.59,0:11:50.84,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}See, you're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.84,0:11:52.09,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Save the trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.09,0:11:55.51,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Someone will be killed if we don't do something right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.56,0:11:58.22,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}And nobody can stop it but Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.27,0:12:00.94,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.94,0:12:02.48,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Look at the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.48,0:12:05.15,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}My sister's match is about to start!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.15,0:12:06.65,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}I have to get back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.82,0:12:08.78,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Can I be of some help?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.07,0:12:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.24,0:12:10.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cheapskate!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.66,0:12:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Japanese?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.99,0:12:16.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.54,0:12:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You speak Japanese?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.76,0:12:21.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.50,0:12:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've lived in Japan before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.09,0:12:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'd like, could you tell me about that\Ncase you were talking about back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.05,0:12:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why should I tell someone like you anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.97,0:12:32.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.84,0:12:34.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Holmes's apprentice, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.44,0:12:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Glass{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.31,0:12:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd you know my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.18,0:12:41.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know me by any{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.77,0:12:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An elementary deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.77,0:12:47.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's white fluid and powder stuck around your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.86,0:12:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the cream and sugar put over strawberries, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.95,0:12:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the container you're holding in your hand\Nhas limes, cucumbers, and mint in it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.24,0:12:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the contents would be the drink called "Pimm's".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.58,0:13:02.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you're a child, they gave you regular\Nlemonade instead of liquor, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.04,0:13:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.13,0:13:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked the vendor to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.46,0:13:11.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a sport where you can routinely get\Nstrawberries and Pimm's while watching...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.92,0:13:13.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has to be tennis at Wimbledon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.18,0:13:17.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today is the women's singles semi-finals.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.68,0:13:21.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first match started at 1:00, and it's past 2:00 now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.43,0:13:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So your sister must be participating in the second match.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.85,0:13:29.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the players is Wang Hai-li whose\Nparents are both Chinese, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.07,0:13:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't look Asian no matter how you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.36,0:13:35.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, it must be her opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.87,0:13:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one dominating Wimbledon for four consecutive years...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.20,0:13:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ranked No.1 in the world and nicknamed the Grass Court Queen...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.41,0:13:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Minerva Glass, that must be your big sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.42,0:13:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.84,0:13:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From your shirt pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.09,0:13:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could see the Wimbledon VIP lounge badge resting inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.76,0:13:57.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.14,0:13:59.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really are Holmes's apprentice, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.26,0:14:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then, will you tell me about the whole story just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.64,0:14:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was eating strawberries a little past noon while watching\Nthe remaining winners practise at Court No. 15, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.40,0:14:17.07,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}So, you like tennis, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.16,0:14:18.99,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.99,0:14:20.58,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}It's quite thrilling!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.74,0:14:22.41,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Thrilling, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.41,0:14:23.50,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Lucky you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.95,0:14:26.87,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Well, you can expect a greater thrill soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:28.00,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.50,0:14:32.96,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}A person is about to be murdered...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.42,0:14:35.34,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Somewhere in London...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.76,0:14:38.59,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Right before your eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.39,0:14:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see that guy's face!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.35,0:14:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His cap covered most of his face so I couldn't get a good look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.90,0:14:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.10,0:14:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did give me this weird paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.94,0:14:53.48,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Tell Scotland Yard...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.48,0:14:55.36,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}It's my Revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.78,0:14:58.57,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}If it doesn't make sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.03,0:15:01.28,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Go to Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.16,0:15:04.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said that and ran off somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.21,0:15:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.76,0:15:16.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can read English, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.09,0:15:17.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.47,0:15:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like some sort of poem, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.89,0:15:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no idea what it's trying to hint at.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.22,0:15:25.10,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Oh, there you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.93,0:15:28.35,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Don't go running off by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.35,0:15:29.48,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}I've been looking for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.39,0:15:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.56,0:15:33.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister's former coach, Ares.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.28,0:15:37.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I hear he used to be a really strong tennis player.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.03,0:15:37.74,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ares Ashley (30)\NMinerva's Former Coach
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.32,0:15:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he was her coach, my mum is on good terms with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.74,0:15:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now he helps us with all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.04,0:15:49.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister's busy with her tours, and our mum's eyes are bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.54,0:15:52.13,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Come on, Apollo...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.13,0:15:53.13,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}Let's get back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.13,0:15:54.25,default01,,0,0,0,,{\be2}She's about to play!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.09,0:15:55.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.26,0:15:57.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.76,0:16:00.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take this to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.80,0:16:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, if he told you to take such a baffling letter to the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.22,0:16:05.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, if he told you to take such a baffling letter to the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.26,0:16:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means he's allowing some time to figure out the puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.10,0:16:10.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's not likely that something's going to happen right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.02,0:16:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.52,0:16:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll give you my mobile number.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.78,0:16:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me know if you figure anything out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.18,0:16:21.17,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,My name is Apollo Glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.76,0:16:22.49,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.04,0:16:23.16,Signs,,0,0,0,,Apollo Glass (8)\NMinvera's Younger Brother
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.87,0:16:25.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Edogawa Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.66,0:16:26.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.12,0:16:29.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure is a name suitable for an apprentice of Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.17,0:16:31.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye then!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.46,0:16:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Promise you'll give me a call!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.46,0:16:35.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.88,0:16:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.17,0:16:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who... were those people?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.63,0:16:42.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there some sort of trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.76,0:16:46.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you're causing trouble even when we're overseas!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.02,0:16:50.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's just like you said...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.14,0:16:53.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.69,0:16:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying he got a mysterious code from some\Nguy giving an advance notice of a murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.28,0:16:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.53,0:17:00.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.57,0:17:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to that kid named Apollo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.78,0:17:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.41,0:17:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.20,0:17:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.58,0:17:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first line says...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.62,0:17:11.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"A rolling bell rises me," so...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.66,0:17:14.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was awakened by the loud sound of a rolling bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.04,0:17:16.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second line is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.38,0:17:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am a long-nosed wizard inhabiting a castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.05,0:17:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The third line is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.22,0:17:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My morsel is a boiled egg that's gone as cold as a corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.05,0:17:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fourth line is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.30,0:17:29.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll finish up my meal by gnawing on a whole pickle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.02,0:17:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fifth line is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.23,0:17:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I remember, I should order a celebratory cake in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.94,0:17:36.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sixth line is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.31,0:17:39.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sound of the bell rings again and stirs up my hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.36,0:17:42.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally, the seventh line is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.53,0:17:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It tells me to finish everything by piercing\Nthe white-colored back with two swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.91,0:17:52.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with that creepy note anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.75,0:17:58.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Supposedly, the man who gave this advance\Nnotice said, "This is my Revelation."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.34,0:18:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By "Revelation," did he mean something like a crime manifesto?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.67,0:18:05.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forget it, forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.47,0:18:07.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probably just some nutjob's idea of a prank!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.22,0:18:10.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I promised Apollo...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.18,0:18:13.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That I'd take this to Scotland Yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.19,0:18:17.40,Signs,,0,0,0,,Wimbledon Centre Court
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.42,0:18:31.92,Signs,,0,0,0,,Minerva Glass (22)\NTennis Player
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.20,0:18:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.85,0:18:49.90,Signs,,0,0,0,,Scotland Yard (London Police HQ)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.85,0:18:53.43,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You're saying that many other people also received that note?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.93,0:18:57.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, all the ones who received those were children?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.94,0:19:03.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now in the station, there are tons\Nof kids and their parents with that note.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.19,0:19:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems like a man wearing a cap with dark skin and dreadlocks...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.11,0:19:12.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had been giving out that note on the\Nstreet, in parks, and various other places!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.66,0:19:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he'd whisper in their ears:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.21,0:19:17.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"A person is about to be murdered in London soon."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.04,0:19:20.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.75,0:19:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall correctly, that Apollo kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.80,0:19:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was told "someone will be killed right before your eyes," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.42,0:19:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.55,0:19:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that man had said the same thing to the other children...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.89,0:19:32.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.14,0:19:33.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.02,0:19:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would mean that someone is going\Nto die in front of each child's eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.39,0:19:40.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.44,0:19:44.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means a large number of people might be killed at once, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.40,0:19:47.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mass murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.57,0:19:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here in London!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.28,0:19:55.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.41,0:19:58.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He plans to carry it out in some place where many people aggregate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.71,0:20:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At this time of year, the tennis at Wimbledon would be suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.84,0:20:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.21,0:20:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since everyone's watching the match oh TV...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.30,0:20:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.71,0:20:13.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of the kids that were handed the note, a fair number\Nof them were wearing racing-style bike helmets...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.05,0:20:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I don't think that's the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.06,0:20:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since they said they were glued to the TV\Neveryday, watching the Tour de France.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.22,0:20:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tour de...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.98,0:20:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.81,0:20:26.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a bike race that's held in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.32,0:20:31.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The broadcasts of the race and\NWimbledon matches air concurrently...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.16,0:20:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you can't watch both of them at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.87,0:20:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that means the British Museum...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.99,0:20:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or Buckingham Palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.29,0:20:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, you guys go check out places where people might gather.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.96,0:20:44.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We may be able to figure something out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.13,0:20:47.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to try and crack the code with the professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.50,0:20:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.80,0:20:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.05,0:20:53.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be eating dinner at the hotel with Diana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.43,0:20:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be back before then!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.93,0:21:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We could've gone and investigated with the\Nothers while trying to solve the code, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.98,0:21:07.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First of all, it's wiser for us to split up and gather information.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.23,0:21:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we have no idea when, where, or what's going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.86,0:21:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, if I tried to decipher the code like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.41,0:21:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd be exposed as Kudou Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.54,0:21:21.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's already a lot of exposure!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.79,0:21:27.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, it started with, "I was awakened\Nby the loud sound of a rolling bell."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.59,0:21:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this possibly refer to an alarm clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.59,0:21:38.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the next line, "I am a long-nosed wizard in a castle..."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.35,0:21:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could refer to a castle somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.35,0:21:44.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The common keywords in lines three, four, and five are food names.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.90,0:21:46.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boiled egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.81,0:21:47.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pickle...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.73,0:21:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.61,0:21:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the sixth line...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.53,0:21:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The sound of the bell rings again," could also mean a clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.45,0:22:00.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "two swords" in the last line may\Nrefer to blades or murder weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.08,0:22:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suppose we think in simple terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.91,0:22:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can take it to mean that near a\Ncastle-esque building are two clock shops...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.96,0:22:13.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Along with a grocery store, a cake shop, and\Na shop that deals with cutlery or weapons...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.17,0:22:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And something will happen at a place like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.38,0:22:17.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any place like that in London?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.43,0:22:18.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's buy a map and find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.56,0:22:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the city of my dreams where Sherlock\NHolmes took the stage — London...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.65,0:22:32.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mystifying note of "Revelation" given to\Nme by{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce by a boy named Apollo...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.44,0:22:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall solve this mystery...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.82,0:22:38.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And put a stop to this crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.57,0:24:02.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hidden behind the "Revelation" are mysterious codes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.45,0:24:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to obtain the deciphering key, we have\Nto scour the roads of London up and down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.04,0:24:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No good!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.75,0:24:10.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My identity's on the verge of being exposed,\Nand Ran's chasing me up and down!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.87,0:24:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.90,0:24:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Big Ben
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:40.07,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look Forward to the Next Episode
